 Description:
Tables organize data into rows and columns using 
<table>, <tr> (table row), <th> (header cell), and <td> (data cell) elements. You can style borders, spacing, and more.



<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Tables</title>
  <style>
    table {
      border-collapse: collapse;
      width: 60%;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    th, td {
      border: 2px solid #264653;
      padding: 12px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    th {
      background-color: #2a9d8f;
      color: white;
    }

    tr:nth-child(even) {
      background-color: #e9ecef;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

